---
title: Perfect Pachamanca Inspired Chicken with Sweet Potato and Bulgur
description: Pachamanca is a much-loved traditional Peruvian family feasting dish that's baked in a special underground oven. No need to start digging though, as this easier stovetop version brings similar flavour by cooking the ingredients slowly until tender.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/HF_Y24_R05_W45_UK_R27142-3_Main_low-bd473d8f.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/66d71644cc7423314feb8983-en-GB.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/perfect-pachamanca-inspired-chicken-66d71644cc7423314feb8983
servings: 2
course: main course
author: Sam Richards
time required: 45m
nutrition:
  calories: 843 kcal
  fat: 34.6 g
  saturated fat: 11.8 g
  carbohydrates: 80.3 g
  sugar: 12.3 g
  protein: 57.8 g
  fiber: 9.5 g
  sodium: 3.2 g
  serving size: 681
---

Slice the @Sweet Potato{1} in half lengthways, then chop into 1cm half moons (no
need to peel). Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{3} (or use a #garlic press{}).
Pick the @Mint{1%bunch} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the
stalks).

Heat a large #saucepan{} on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}.
Once hot, lay the @British Chicken Thighs{4} flat in the pan. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry until the chicken is browned, ~{4-5%minutes} each
side.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging.

Once the chicken is browned, add the sweet potato. Stir in the
@Chipotle Paste{20%grams} (add less if you'd prefer things milder),
@Dried Oregano{1%sachet} and garlic. Stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @Red Wine Vinegar{12%ml}, half the @Chicken Stock Paste{20%grams},
half the mint and the @Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water{200%ml} for the sauce (see
pantry for both amounts) to the chicken. Stir well to combine. Bring to the
boil, then lower the heat to medium. Simmer until the sauce has thickened and
the chicken is cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, pour the @Water{220%ml} for the bulgur (see pantry for amount) into
another large saucepan, stir in the remaining chicken stock paste and bring to
the boil. Stir in the @Bulgur Wheat{120%grams}, bring back up to the boil and
simmer for ~{1%minute}. Pop a #lid{} on the pan and remove from the heat. Leave
to the side for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

When the sauce has thickened and the chicken is cooked through, add the
@Baby Spinach{40%grams} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping
hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Taste the sauce and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Share the bulgur wheat between your serving bowls and top with the pachamanca
inspired chicken and sauce. Crumble over the @Greek Style Salad Cheese{50%grams}
and sprinkle with the remaining mint to finish. Enjoy!